
<!-- compliance:pci -->
## Compliance: PCI DSS v4.0

- NEVER store full PAN unencrypted; tokenize or vault.
- NEVER log full PAN — mask to first 6 + last 4 max.
- WHEN expanding scope (new component touching cardholder data), document in scope map.
- WHEN designing networks, isolate CDE (cardholder data environment) via segmentation.
- Quarterly ASV scan + annual penetration test scheduled.
- WHEN handling sensitive auth data (CVV, PIN, magnetic stripe), never store post-authorization.
- Encryption keys rotated annually; managed via approved KMS.
